===Alternative forms===
* A graphical variant <span class="skin-invert-image">[[File:Ufa70.svg|x20px]]</span> exists for this character, with the dots on either side of the bottom component {{l|mul|亚}} written as right angles ({{l|mul|𠃊}} and {{l|mul|𠃎}}) instead of the usual dots ({{l|mul|丶}} and {{l|mul|㇒}}).
** In the historical [[w:Kangxi dictionary|Kangxi dictionary]], derived characters of {{lang|mul|並}} such as {{l|mul|sc=Kore|掽}} and {{l|mul|sc=Kore|湴}} are written using this form but not the character {{lang|mul|並}} itself.
*** Additionally, the Kangxi Dictionary frequently used the variant [[𠀤]], which is ironically not present in the dictionary itself.
** This variant is also the {{zh-l|舊字形}} form of {{lang|mul|並}} used in printed publications before 1965 in mainland China.
** A [[w:CJK Compatibility Ideographs|CJK compatibility ideograph]] exists at <code>U+FA70</code> for this variant that is used in North Korean computing. An [[w:Ideographic Variation Sequence|Ideographic Variation Sequence]] also exists as <code>U+4E26 U+E0101</code>, producing &#x4e26;&#xe0101;.

